<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-22T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-22T12:00:00-05:00" n="788" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d788">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.7311/12</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-22T18:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3696. My 2987, January 3, 11 a.m., and previous telegrams.<note n="1" xml:id="d788fn1">Not printed.</note> The Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs of Montenegro has just informed me that the King proposes to
                            name as envoy extraordinary and minister <pb facs="0879" n="787" xml:id="pg_787"/> plenipotentiary to United States, General Doctor
                                <persName corresp="#p_GGA1">Antoine Gvosdenovitch</persName>,
                            aide-de-camp to the King, and would be glad to know if this person would
                            be <hi rend="italic">persona grata</hi> to the Federal Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>